5:
Sorry to bug you like this out of
nowhere. I just really need to ask
you something.
9:
I'm guessing it's something you
don't want others knowing about,
seeing as you came all the way to
Starview.
13: Ah, yeah, well, you got me there...
16:
I just... I want you guys to help Mili.
She seems to have a lot on her mind
lately.
19:
Whenever Rem, Ram, or I ask her
what's up, she just gives us the
same answer—that she's fine.
22:
Well... She is in a different world.
There's bound to be a lot on her
mind.
26:
Some things are harder to talk
about with people you're close to,
right? That's where we come in.
30:
So you'll help? Thanks, Alk! I owe you,
man!
35:
Now, where might Emilia be at this
hour?
45:
...It's no use. I can't find that room
from last time. Where could it be...
48:
(Should I continue forward? Or
would it be better to exit and start
again from the beginning...)
51:
(For now, let's press onward. Our
predicament is affecting everyone,
not just me. I need more
information.)
54:
(Perhaps the spirits could tell me
something.)
57:
Can you hear me? I have something
to ask you all.
62:
Hey, why're we always everyone's
errand boys? I say we let that
Subaru kid deal with his own
problems....
66:
Come on, if you can't count on
friends when you're in trouble, who
can you count on? Besides, it seems
like Subaru's been through a lot.
69:
*sigh* You just love stickin' your
nose in everyone's business, don't
you... Whatever. Let's just hurry up
and find her.
86: What are you all doing here?
90:
Are you okay? You're not hurt
anywhere, are you?
93:
No, I'm fine... That monster just
knocked me down, that's all.
98:
Regardless, you should rest! Leave
the rest to Alk and—
107: Now THAT'S what I call power!
114:
Um, thank you for coming to my
rescue. I would have been in trouble
on my own.
118:
...Why were you so far down in the
Kaleidoscope alone to begin with?
122:
While I certainly recognize your
combat skills, I cannot condone
such rash behavior...
125:
I apologize... I merely wished to find
a clue as to how we can return to
our world.
128:
But I didn't want to burden Subaru
and the others either...
133:
Well, all that did was make him
worry more...
142:
This ain't the place for chatting. We
should head back to the surface.
146:
Wait, you were looking for a way to
return to your world through the
Kaleidoscope?!
150:
A book I found mentioned that
several individuals have sought a
way home through that exact
method...
156:
W-well, uhhh... If that's true, it's gotta
be one of the more risky options...
160:
I can only assume you went in
knowing the dangers of such an
approach. But what would compel
you to take such a risk?
166:
Back home, there's something I
want—no, something I NEED to do.
169:
Something very, very important that
could alter the fates of countless
people.
172:
And you see this thing as your duty, I
suppose?
177:
...I simply worry that I will not be able
to undo anything that happens in
my absence...
181:
I apologize. It seems I have caused
you all trouble.
184:
Actually, we may be able to assist
you with your problem.
187:
The World Flipper can be used to
traverse worlds. At the very least, it
should be more reliable than the
Kaleidoscope.
189:
I too am searching for my home
world. Perhaps we could work
together to achieve our shared goal.
193: But... why would you help me?
197:
What? Should we not help our fellow
adventurers?
201:
Besides, Subaru asked us for our
help.
210:
Like I said, he's been worried about
you. It seems like you've been taking
on more than you should.
212:
Maybe he wouldn't worry so much if
you relied on him and the others
once in a while. Isn't that right,
Subaru?
218:
Come on, your detection skills are
way too OP!
229: Please, Mili... let me help you!
234: I think you mean, "let US help you."
238:
I'm sorry. I should have noticed you
were worrying, Subaru.
241:
I was so focused on what I was
trying to do that I was completely
oblivious to what was going on
around me.
246:
You need not rush yourself. You
have your friends to help you.
249:
And we will also be here to assist
you. Have faith in us, Emilia.
253:
You are all such interesting
individuals...
257:
Thank you... From now on, I will be
sure to ask you for help when I need
it.
260: After all, I don't want to worry Subaru.
